.TH replace-string 2
.XI replace-string - "\*(C0Replace string with new string"
.SH NAME
replace-string \- Replace string with new string
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.I n
\fBreplace-string\fR \*(C0
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B replace-string
replaces all occurrences of one string with another string. The replacement starts at the current location of the
cursor and goes to the end of the current buffer.
.PP
A numeric argument positive \fIn\fR limits the number of strings replaced to \fIn\fR. A negative argument \fIn\fR
limits the number of lines in which the replacement may take place, e.g. a value of -15 restricts the replacement of
the string to the next 15 lines from the current cursor position.
.PP
.Ht $result 5
is set to a list giving the number of substitutions, a replace mode of 'a' for all and the replace with string.
.SH NOTES
When using
.Hl "regular expressions" RegularExpressions 2
the replacement string can be dynamically generated creating a far more powerful tool for automating complex changes, 
see section on \fISyntax of Replacement Expressions\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
